HEADWORD: Lutein
<hw>Lu"te*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From corpus
<ets>lute</ets>um.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance
of a strongly marked yellow color, extracted from the yolk of eggs, and
from the tissue of the corpus luteum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

